<subSubSection pageId="163" pageNumber="766" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="163.[780,1373,2548,2971]" pageId="163" pageNumber="766">
<taxonomicName box="[784,1040,2627,2656]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Grammomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="163" pageNumber="766" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="selousi">Grammomys selousi</taxonomicName>
1s distinguished from similar co-occurring congeners on chromosomal grounds; chromosomal complement has 2n = 49-50, FN = 56. Recent molecular study showed its genetic distance and revealed a high cryptic diversity in the genus. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="163" pageNumber="766" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="163" pageNumber="766" startId="163.[780,952,2903,2932]" targetBox="[166,757,2547,2959]" targetPageId="163">
<paragraph blockId="163.[780,1373,2548,2971]" pageId="163" pageNumber="766">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[780,956,2903,2932]" pageId="163" pageNumber="766">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from Kitchi Forest, EC Tanzania.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="163" pageNumber="766" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="163.[166,1372,2981,3364]" pageId="163" pageNumber="766">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,418,2981,3010]" pageId="163" pageNumber="766">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Measurements of type specimen given by C. Denys and colleagues in 2011 were as follows: Head—body 107 mm, tail 167 mm, ear 17-5 mm, hindfoot 23-5 mm. Fur of Selous’s Thicket Ratis yellow brown above, with creamy-white belly. Tail is very long (156% of head-body length), semi-prehensile, and tufted. Lacks a white post-auricular spot.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
